Gojoseon-Han War

(109-108 BC) Gojoseon Han dynasty Defeat

Gojoseon is annexed by the Han dynasty, which installs the Four Commanderies of Han in its former lands.

End of the Three Kingdoms of Korea

Establishment of Andong Protectorate

Goguryeo and Baekje swear fealty to Silla, thereby forming Unified Silla

Beginning of territorial disputes between Silla and Tang

King Bojang Goryeo–Khitan War

(993, 1010, 1018–1019) Goryeo Liao dynasty Victory

The Khitan Liao dynasty cedes territory around the Yalu River basin to Goryeo

Goryeo pays tribute to the Liao dynasty to establish diplomatic relations

Peace ensues between Goryeo and Liao, and Liao never attacks Goryeo again
